cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a new method for unsupervised learning of sparse representations using autoencoders. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The method is applied to image data, specifically patches of the CIFAR10 dataset, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimization process and the use of hyperparameters, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of sparsity, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
